WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:01.830
In service operations workspace,

1
00:00:02.079 --> 00:00:06.010
you can save personal lists to quickly return to the views you use most often,

2
00:00:06.409 --> 00:00:08.529
including your filters and column layout.

3
00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:12.869
To create a personal list,

4
00:00:13.369 --> 00:00:16.190
start by building the filter conditions you want for your list.

5
00:00:16.370 --> 00:00:17.389
In this example,

6
00:00:17.569 --> 00:00:20.850
I am building a list of on hold incidents assigned to my group.

7
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:24.540
Before you save your list,

8
00:00:24.790 --> 00:00:27.200
you can set up how you want the list to be displayed.

9
00:00:29.260 --> 00:00:31.290
You can add or remove columns

10
00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:34.860
and reorder them so the most useful information appears first.

11
00:00:38.250 --> 00:00:40.439
Once you've got the list set up the way you like it,

12
00:00:40.770 --> 00:00:42.080
you're ready to save.

13
00:00:42.490 --> 00:00:45.029
Click the gear icon to open the list actions menu,

14
00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:46.669
then choose save as.

15
00:00:50.959 --> 00:00:53.439
Give the list a name so it's easy to find later.

16
00:00:55.049 --> 00:00:56.189
Then click save

17
00:00:58.310 --> 00:01:01.180
The saved list now appears under the My List tab,

18
00:01:01.319 --> 00:01:05.500
and you can return to this view at any time without rebuilding the filters or layout.

19
00:01:05.720 --> 00:01:07.080
If you need to make changes later,

20
00:01:07.199 --> 00:01:11.500
head back to the List actions menu where you can rename your list,

21
00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:13.339
save or duplicate your list,

22
00:01:13.639 --> 00:01:14.459
delete it

23
00:01:14.610 --> 00:01:16.459
or adjust which columns are displayed.